page.title: 16Heslington Tilmire
page.content: {Line C-}The southern edge of the Tilmire:- The third transect was five hundred metres south of the golf course line. The area was bounded by cultivated fields and a small oak wood.It had more plants, flowers, shrubs, trees and flying insects than the northern edge of the Tilmire.Some insects such as the dung beetle and bush cricket we found only in this spot.We found- {Grasses:_}soft meadow, meadow and red fescue, common rye, rough meadow, common reed, horsetail, common rush, common meadow, purple moor, couch. {Plants, shrubs,trees:_}creeping buttercup,elder,moss,clover,speedwell, lady's bedstraw, thistle, dock, oak stinging nettle, wood sorrel,hawthorn, duckweed,rhododendron.{Insects:_ greenfly,dungfly,woodlouse,grasshopper bluebottles,bumblebee,earthworm,wasp.
